 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Comparing Marani* and Marani-Inspired Models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- **Summary**: This document compares the original method from [Marani et al. (2021)](https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.2105482118) and the Marani-inspired method for modeling the exceedance probabilities of respiratory viral epidemics. \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Data Required:** `epidemics_marani_240816.xlsx`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- **Author**: Ganqi Li (ganqi.li.25@dartmouth.edu)\n",
    "- **Updated**: Sep 10, 2024"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import yaml\n",
    "from scipy.integrate import quad\n",
    "from scipy.stats import genpareto\n",
    "from scipy.optimize import minimize\n",
    "\n",
    "## repeated printouts\n",
    "from IPython.core.interactiveshell import InteractiveShell\n",
    "InteractiveShell.ast_node_interactivity = \"all\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set filepaths\n",
    "rawdata_dir = Path(\"../../data/raw\").resolve()\n",
    "cleandata_dir = Path(\"../../data/clean\").resolve()\n",
    "figdir = Path(\"../../output/exceedance_figures\").resolve()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Prepare respiratory viral epidemic data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "## Read epidemic data from Marani et al. \n",
    "df = pd.read_excel(rawdata_dir / \"epidemics_marani_240816.xlsx\")\n",
    "df = df.sort_values(by='year_start', ascending=True).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Subset to respiratory viral epidemics\n",
    "df_resp_viral = df[df['disease'].isin(['influenza', 'covid-19', 'mers', 'sars'])\n",
    "                  ].reset_index(drop=True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "## Display all respiratory viral epidemics between 1500-present\n",
    "# df_resp_viral"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Set up exceedance probabilities from Madhav"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ## Create Madhav exceedance with Table 4\n",
    "# severity = [0.001, 0.002, 7.2, 28, 45, 86, 150, 200, 220, 250, 280]\n",
    "# exceedance = [0.2, 0.1, 0.05, 0.02857, 0.02, 0.01, 0.005, 0.003, 0.002, 0.0015, 0.001]\n",
    "\n",
    "# df_madhav = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "#     \"severity\": severity,\n",
    "#     \"exceedance\": exceedance\n",
    "# })\n",
    "\n",
    "# ## Save to exceedance results folder\n",
    "# df_madhav.to_excel(\cleandata_dir / "exceedance_results" / "madhav_original.xlsx\", index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ## Update severeity with 0.01 threshold \n",
    "# severity = [0.01, 7.2, 28, 45, 86, 150, 200, 220, 250, 280]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "## Read Madhav exceedance results from '03_resp_viral_comp'\n",
    "df_madhav = pd.read_excel(cleandata_dir \"exceedance_results\" / \"madhav_original.xlsx\")\n",
    "\n",
    "## Set severeity points automatically \n",
    "plot_madhav_points = False  ## CHANGE METHOD HERE\n",
    "\n",
    "if plot_madhav_points:\n",
    "    severity = [0.01, 7.2, 28, 45, 86, 150, 200, 220, 250, 280]\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    severity = [0.01, 0.04, 0.07, 0.08, 0.1, 0.4, 0.7, 1, 4, 7, 8, 10, \n",
    "                15, 20, 28, 40, 45, 70, 86, 100, 120, 150, 170, 190, \n",
    "                200, 220, 230, 240, 250, 260, 270, 280]\n",
    "\n",
    "## Set up severity points manually\n",
    "# severity = df_madhav['severity']\n",
    "# severity = [0.01, 7.2, 28, 45, 86, 150, 200, 220, 250, 280]\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Calibrate model with Marani* method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Note:** Unlike Marani et al., we directly model the severity (deaths per population) instead of the intensity (deaths per population per year) of epidemics. We follow their methodology in using data from 1600-1945 to calibrate the generalized Pareto tail, and multiply the arrival rate of all epidemics in the past 20 years (2000-2019) and the probability of an epidemic being severe conditional on arrival during 1600-1945 to obtain the arrival rate of severe epidemics above the threshold of 0.01 SMU. We refer to this as the Marani* method."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "## Subset epidemic data to 1600-1945\n",
    "df_marani_star = df_resp_viral[(df_resp_viral[\"year_start\"] >= 1600) & \n",
    "                               (df_resp_viral[\"year_start\"] <= 1945)].reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Set severity threshold to 0.01 SMU\n",
    "thresh = 0.01\n",
    "\n",
    "## Subset to threshold-exceeding respiratory viral epidemics\n",
    "df_marani_star_exceed = df_marani_star[df_marani_star['severity_smu'] >= thresh].reset_index(drop=True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
